gate: OPEN
v:4 role:dev x:frontend
task: S88 T4 — Settings: trust device toggle with security warning
requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
sprint: S88

context: |
  User must consciously choose "enter without biometry" and acknowledge risk.
  Copy should be plain language (RU/EN/BG): anyone with the phone can open
  the app; recommend Face ID for shared or lost devices.

steps:
  1. In MainSettingsSection (Tauri only), add toggle "Remember session on
     this device" / trust device (maps to local_trust_device).
  2. On enable: modal with warning text + Confirm / Cancel (no silent toggle).
  3. On confirm: set local_trust_device true, local_use_biometry false,
     clear biometric credentials from vault, migrate current session to
     durable storage (T3).
  4. On disable trust: return to standard login-on-next-open or offer
     biometry opt-in again.
  5. Helper text under toggle: password only after sign-out or token failure.
  6. i18n keys: settings.trustDevice, settings.trustDeviceWarningTitle,
     settings.trustDeviceWarningBody, settings.trustDeviceConfirm.

out:
  - src/screens/settings/components/MainSettingsSection.tsx
  - locale JSON (ru, en, bg)

done:
  - Cannot enable trust device without confirming warning dialog.
  - Biometry toggle and trust toggle are mutually exclusive in UI.
  - Warning copy visible and understandable for non-technical users.
  - Turning trust off does not leave stale durable token without user awareness.
